sentences: Ellie Blanche Delvaux (French pronunciation: ​[eli dɛlvo]; born 10 June 1999), better known as simply Blanche [blɑ̃ʃ], is a Belgian singer and songwriter.
She represented Belgium in the Eurovision Song Contest 2017 in Ukraine with the song "City Lights", finishing in fourth place.
Blanche previously competed on season five of The Voice Belgique, where she was a member of Team Cats on Trees.
Ellie Delvaux was born in Belgium, on 10 June 1999.
